## When making changes:
1. Always validate inputs at system boundaries: file sizes before upload, API keys before external calls
2. Handle partial failures — never throw away successful work because one item failed
3. Show real progress during long operations (X of Y, not just a spinner)
4. Remove dead code — grep for unused types/interfaces/exports before finishing

## Watchdog QA Agent
- `npm run watchdog` — standalone script that continuously tests all endpoints
- Config: `scripts/watchdog.config.json` (all overridable via `WATCHDOG_*` env vars)
- Requires `WATCHDOG_EMAIL` / `WATCHDOG_PASSWORD` env vars for authenticated API tests
- Reports to `watchdog-report.json` (gitignored)

## Security Agent
- `npm run security` — continuous security audit across 14 categories
- `npm run security:once` — single scan with exit codes (0=clean, 1=high, 2=critical) for CI
- Config: `scripts/security.config.json`
- Reports to `security-report.json` (gitignored)

## Stress Test Agent
- `npm run stress-test` — simulates N concurrent users performing realistic flows
- Reports per-endpoint metrics (requests, success%, p50/p95/p99 latency, error rate, throughput)
- Config: `scripts/stress-test.config.json` (overridable via `STRESS_*` env vars)
